******
[2] VSV outbreak summary to date
Date: Fri 1 May 2020
Source: Feedstuffs [abridged, edited]
https://www.feedstuffs.com/news/vesicular-stomatitis-outbreak-expanding


The 2020 vesicular stomatitis virus (VSV) outbreak is growing, with the Texas Animal Health Commission (TAHC) confirming the virus on an El Paso County, Texas, premises, marking the 3rd case of VSV in Texas this year [2020].

In a 29 Apr 2020 situation update, the US Department of Agriculture's (USDA) Animal & Plant Health Inspection Service (APHIS) reported that, to date, 14 premises have been identified in 6 counties across 3 states: New Mexico, Arizona, and Texas.

APHIS confirmed both the VSV-Indiana and VSV-New Jersey serotypes have been identified this year [2020]. VSV-Indiana occurred in the US in 2019, while VSV-New Jersey was last isolated in the US in the 2014-2015 outbreak, APHIS said, noting that both serotypes are known to circulate in endemic cycles in southern Mexico. The last US outbreak involving both serotypes occurred in 1997-98.

The US 2020 VSV outbreak began on 13 Apr 2020 when NVSL confirmed the 1st VSV-positive premises in New Mexico. Arizona's index case was confirmed 22 Apr [2020], and Texas's 1st case was confirmed 23 Apr 2020.

[Byline: Tim Lundeen]

