[The outbreak of vesicular stomatitis virus (VSV) in the United States is a mixed outbreak. In the state of Texas, it is a mixed outbreak as well. Texas has both Indiana serotype and New Jersey serotype. Most of Texas thus far appears to be New Jersey serotype, while this case, bordering New Mexico, is the same serotype as what is in New Mexico, the Indiana serotype.

Use of horse-approved fly/mosquito spray may also help reduce the insect burden around the animals. - Mod.TG

